{"type":"text","timestamp":1775884782679,"sessionID":"ses_28507894fffenXvgpComB0RfPx","part":{"id":"prt_d7afb4a41001g7CJdqqtqHJJ6h","messageID":"msg_d7afb25e30017vrmKhIzx1FiwF","sessionID":"ses_28507894fffenXvgpComB0RfPx","type":"text","text":"Now I'll create the delta-spec.md file for AR-020 in the correct location:","time":{"start":1775884782678,"end":1775884782678}}}
{"type":"text","timestamp":1775884892958,"sessionID":"ses_28507894fffenXvgpComB0RfPx","part":{"id":"prt_d7afc11430011Ct6NRBcsQjvIb","messageID":"msg_d7afb25e30017vrmKhIzx1FiwF","sessionID":"ses_28507894fffenXvgpComB0RfPx","type":"text","text":" pass","time":{"start":1775884892947,"end":1775884892947}}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775884892972,"sessionID":"ses_28507894fffenXvgpComB0RfPx","part":{"id":"prt_d7afb4c58001OKs07H8hls8CyE","messageID":"msg_d7afb25e30017vrmKhIzx1FiwF","sessionID":"ses_28507894fffenXvgpComB0RfPx","type":"tool","tool":"write","callID":"toolu_functions.write:9","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-kimi-k2.5_20260410T163138Z/changes/AR-020/delta-spec.md","content":"# Delta Spec: AR-020 — CLI Pack Command\n\n## Overview\n\n**AR ID:** AR-020  \n**Module:** cmd/cli  \n**Language:** Python  \n**Size:** M  \n\nImplement the `pack` command for the AgentCube CLI. This command validates and prepares an agent workspace, merges CLI overrides into metadata, optionally generates a Dockerfile, and reports paths.\n\n---\n\n## Requirements\n\n### Requirement: Pack command options and defaults\n\nThe system SHALL provide a `pack` command with well-defined options and sensible defaults.\n\n#### Scenario: Default options when pack runs without arguments\n- **GIVEN** the user runs `pack` without specifying any options\n- **WHEN** the command is executed\n- **THEN** the CLI SHALL use the following defaults:\n  - `workspace` = `\".\"` (current directory, from `-f` / `--workspace`, `str`)\n  - `agent_name` = `None` (from `--agent-name`, `Optional[str]`)\n  - `language` = `None` (from `--language`, `Optional[str]`)\n  - `entrypoint` = `None` (from `--entrypoint`, `Optional[str]`)\n  - `port` = `None` (from `--port`, `Optional[int]`)\n  - `build_mode` = `None` (from `--build-mode`, `Optional[str]`)\n  - `description` = `None` (from `--description`, `Optional[str]`)\n  - `output` = `None` (from `--output`, `Optional[str]`)\n  - `verbose` = `False` (from `--verbose`, command-local `bool`)\n\n#### Scenario: Override workspace path\n- **GIVEN** the user runs `pack -f /path/to/agent`\n- **WHEN** the command is executed\n- **THEN** the CLI SHALL resolve the workspace path to `/path/to/agent`\n\n#### Scenario: Override agent name\n- **GIVEN** the user runs `pack --agent-name my-custom-agent`\n- **WHEN** the command is executed\n- **THEN** the CLI SHALL pass `agent_name=\"my-custom-agent\"` to `PackRuntime.pack()`\n\n#### Scenario: Override language\n- **GIVEN** the user runs `pack --language java`\n- **WHEN** the command is executed\n- **THEN** the CLI SHALL pass `language=\"java\"` to `PackRuntime.pack()`\n\n#### Scenario: Override port\n- **GIVEN** the user runs `pack --port 9090`\n- **WHEN** the command is executed\n- **THEN** the CLI SHALL pass `port=9090` to `PackRuntime.pack()`\n\n---\n\n### Requirement: Workspace validation\n\nThe system SHALL validate that the workspace path exists, is a directory, and contains appropriate source files based on the detected or specified language.\n\n#### Scenario: Missing workspace directory\n- **GIVEN** the user runs `pack -f /nonexistent/path`\n- **WHEN** `PackRuntime._validate_workspace_structure` is called\n- **THEN** the system SHALL raise `ValueError` with a message indicating the directory does not exist\n- **AND** the CLI SHALL print \"Error packaging agent: {message}\" in red\n- **AND** the CLI SHALL exit with code `1`\n\n#### Scenario: Workspace path is a file\n- **GIVEN** the user runs `pack -f /path/to/file.txt` where `file.txt` exists but is not a directory\n- **WHEN** `PackRuntime._validate_workspace_structure` is called\n- **THEN** the system SHALL raise `ValueError` with a message indicating the path is not a directory\n- **AND** the CLI SHALL exit with code `1`\n\n#### Scenario: Python workspace without Python files\n- **GIVEN** the workspace directory exists\n- **AND** `metadata.language == \"python\"`\n- **WHEN** no `*.py` files exist in the workspace root\n- **THEN** `PackRuntime._validate_python_compatibility` SHALL raise `ValueError(\"No Python files found in workspace\")`\n- **AND** the CLI SHALL exit with code `1`\n\n#### Scenario: Java workspace without pom.xml\n- **GIVEN** the workspace directory exists\n- **AND** `metadata.language == \"java\"`\n- **WHEN** no `pom.xml` file exists in the workspace root\n- **THEN** `PackRuntime._validate_java_compatibility` SHALL raise `ValueError` indicating Maven project file is missing\n- **AND** the CLI SHALL exit with code `1`\n\n#### Scenario: Valid Python workspace\n- **GIVEN** the workspace directory exists and contains at least one `*.py` file\n- **AND** `metadata.language == \"python\"`\n- **WHEN** `PackRuntime._validate_workspace_structure` runs\n- **THEN** no exception SHALL be raised\n- **AND** validation SHALL pass\n\n#### Scenario: Valid Java workspace\n- **GIVEN** the workspace directory exists and contains `pom.xml`\n- **AND** `metadata.language == \"java\"`\n- **WHEN** `PackRuntime._validate_workspace_structure` runs\n- **THEN** no exception SHALL be raised\n- **AND** validation SHALL pass\n\n---\n\n### Requirement: Metadata management\n\nThe system SHALL load existing metadata, create new metadata if missing, apply CLI option overrides, and persist the final metadata to YAML.\n\n#### Scenario: Load existing agent_metadata.yaml\n- **GIVEN** the workspace contains `agent_metadata.yaml`\n- **WHEN** `PackRuntime._load_or_create_metadata` is called\n- **THEN** the system SHALL load the YAML file\n- **AND** parse it into an `AgentMetadata` Pydantic model\n- **AND** return the populated `AgentMetadata` instance\n\n#### Scenario: Fallback to agent.yaml\n- **GIVEN** the workspace does not contain `agent_metadata.yaml`\n- **AND** the workspace contains `agent.yaml`\n- **WHEN** `PackRuntime._load_or_create_metadata` is called\n- **THEN** the system SHALL load `agent.yaml`\n- **AND** parse it into an `AgentMetadata` Pydantic model\n\n#### Scenario: Fallback to metadata.yaml\n- **GIVEN** the workspace does not contain `agent_metadata.yaml` or `agent.yaml`\n- **AND** the workspace contains `metadata.yaml`\n- **WHEN** `PackRuntime._load_or_create_metadata` is called\n- **THEN** the system SHALL load `metadata.yaml`\n- **AND** parse it into an `AgentMetadata` Pydantic model\n\n#### Scenario: Create new metadata when no file exists\n- **GIVEN** the workspace does not contain any metadata file\n- **AND** no `agent_name` is provided via CLI\n- **WHEN** `PackRuntime._load_or_create_metadata` is called\n- **THEN** the system SHALL derive the agent name from the workspace directory name\n- **AND** create a new `AgentMetadata` with default values:\n  - `agent_name` = directory name\n  - `language` = `python` (from `MetadataOptions` default)\n  - `entrypoint` = inferred from workspace contents\n  - `port` = `8080`\n  - `build_mode` = `local`\n\n#### Scenario: Apply CLI option overrides\n- **GIVEN** existing metadata with `agent_name=\"old-name\"`, `port=8080`\n- **AND** CLI options: `--agent-name new-name --port 9090`\n- **WHEN** `PackRuntime._apply_option_overrides` is called\n- **THEN** the returned metadata SHALL have:\n  - `agent_name` = `\"new-name\"`\n  - `port` = `9090`\n  - other fields SHALL remain unchanged from original metadata\n\n#### Scenario: Save metadata to agent_metadata.yaml\n- **GIVEN** metadata has been loaded/created and potentially modified\n- **WHEN** `PackRuntime._update_pack_metadata` is called\n- **THEN** the system SHALL write to `{workspace}/agent_metadata.yaml`\n- **AND** use `yaml.dump` with:\n  - `default_flow_style=False`\n  - `indent=2`\n  - `sort_keys=False`\n- **AND** exclude `None` fields via `model_dump(exclude_none=True)`\n\n---\n\n### Requirement: Language compatibility validation\n\nThe system SHALL validate that the workspace structure is compatible with the specified language.\n\n#### Scenario: Supported languages\n- **GIVEN** the language field is set to `\"python\"` or `\"java\"` (case-insensitive)\n- **WHEN** `AgentMetadata` validators run\n- **THEN** the value SHALL be normalized to lowercase\n- **AND** validation SHALL pass\n\n#### Scenario: Unsupported language\n- **GIVEN** the language field is set to `\"ruby\"`\n- **WHEN** `AgentMetadata` validators run\n- **THEN** Pydantic SHALL reject the value with validation error\n- **AND** raise `ValidationError` with message indicating supported languages are `python` and `java`\n\n#### Scenario: Supported build modes\n- **GIVEN** the build_mode field is set to `\"local\"` or `\"cloud\"` (case-insensitive)\n- **WHEN** `AgentMetadata` validators run\n- **THEN** the value SHALL be normalized to lowercase\n- **AND** validation SHALL pass\n\n#### Scenario: Unsupported build mode\n- **GIVEN** the build_mode field is set to `\"hybrid\"`\n- **WHEN** `AgentMetadata` validators run\n- **THEN** Pydantic SHALL reject the value with validation error\n- **AND** raise `ValidationError` with message indicating supported modes are `local` and `cloud`\n\n#### Scenario: Valid port range\n- **GIVEN** the port field is set to `8080`\n- **WHEN** `AgentMetadata` validators run\n- **THEN** validation SHALL pass\n\n#### Scenario: Invalid port range\n- **GIVEN** the port field is set to `70000` (outside 1-65535)\n- **WHEN** `AgentMetadata` validators run\n- **THEN** Pydantic SHALL reject the value with validation error\n- **AND** raise `ValidationError` indicating port must be between 1 and 65535\n\n---\n\n### Requirement: Entrypoint inference\n\nThe system SHALL infer the entrypoint command when not explicitly provided.\n\n#### Scenario: Infer Python entrypoint\n- **GIVEN** `metadata.language == \"python\"`\n- **AND** the workspace contains `main.py`\n- **AND** no entrypoint is specified in metadata or CLI\n- **WHEN** `PackRuntime._infer_entrypoint` is called\n- **THEN** the system SHALL return `python main.py`\n\n#### Scenario: Infer Java entrypoint\n- **GIVEN** `metadata.language == \"java\"`\n- **AND** the workspace contains `pom.xml`\n- **AND** no entrypoint is specified in metadata or CLI\n- **WHEN** `PackRuntime._infer_entrypoint` is called\n- **THEN** the system SHALL return a Maven-based entrypoint\n\n#### Scenario: Cannot infer entrypoint\n- **GIVEN** `metadata.language == \"python\"`\n- **AND** no clear main file can be identified\n- **WHEN** `PackRuntime._infer_entrypoint` is called\n- **THEN** the system SHALL return a sensible default or raise an appropriate error\n\n---\n\n### Requirement: Dependency processing\n\nThe system SHALL process language-specific dependencies as part of the pack operation.\n\n#### Scenario: Process Python dependencies\n- **GIVEN** `metadata.language == \"python\"`\n- **AND** `metadata.requirements_file` is `requirements.txt`\n- **WHEN** `PackRuntime._process_dependencies` is called\n- **THEN** `PackRuntime._process_python_dependencies` SHALL be invoked\n- **AND** it SHALL validate that `requirements.txt` exists\n- **AND** it SHALL log the dependencies being processed if verbose\n\n#### Scenario: Process Java dependencies\n- **GIVEN** `metadata.language == \"java\"`\n- **WHEN** `PackRuntime._process_dependencies` is called\n- **THEN** `PackRuntime._process_java_dependencies` SHALL be invoked\n- **AND** it SHALL validate Maven project structure\n\n---\n\n### Requirement: Dockerfile generation\n\nThe system SHALL generate a Dockerfile based on the metadata configuration.\n\n#### Scenario: Generate Python Dockerfile\n- **GIVEN** `metadata.language == \"python\"`\n- **AND** `metadata.port == 8080`\n- **AND** `metadata.entrypoint == \"python main.py\"`\n- **WHEN** `PackRuntime._generate_python_dockerfile` is called\n- **THEN** it SHALL return a Dockerfile string containing:\n  - `FROM python:3.x-slim` or similar base image\n  - `WORKDIR /app`\n  - `COPY requirements.txt .` and `RUN pip install`\n  - `COPY . .`\n  - `EXPOSE 8080`\n  - `CMD [\"python\", \"main.py\"]`\n\n#### Scenario: Generate Java Dockerfile\n- **GIVEN** `metadata.language == \"java\"`\n- **AND** `metadata.port == 8080`\n- **WHEN** `PackRuntime._generate_java_dockerfile` is called\n- **THEN** it SHALL return a Dockerfile string containing:\n  - Multi-stage build with Maven\n  - Build stage compiling the project\n  - Runtime stage with JRE\n  - `EXPOSE 8080`\n  - CMD to run the JAR\n\n#### Scenario: Skip Dockerfile generation when output path is None\n- **GIVEN** `output` option is `None`\n- **WHEN** `PackRuntime.pack` runs\n- **THEN** `_generate_dockerfile` MAY be called\n- **AND** the resulting Dockerfile path SHALL be `None`\n\n---\n\n### Requirement: Output path preparation\n\nThe system SHALL prepare the output path for the packaged workspace.\n\n#### Scenario: Default output path\n- **GIVEN** `output` option is `None`\n- **AND** workspace path is `/home/user/my-agent`\n- **WHEN** `PackRuntime._prepare_output_path` is called\n- **THEN** it SHALL return `{workspace_path}` (same as input workspace)\n\n#### Scenario: Custom output path\n- **GIVEN** `output` option is `/tmp/packed-agent`\n- **WHEN** `PackRuntime._prepare_output_path` is called\n- **THEN** it SHALL create the directory if it doesn't exist\n- **AND** return `Path(\"/tmp/packed-agent\")`\n\n#### Scenario: Output path is file\n- **GIVEN** `output` option points to an existing file (not directory)\n- **WHEN** `PackRuntime._prepare_output_path` is called\n- **THEN** it SHALL raise `ValueError` indicating the path must be a directory\n\n---\n\n### Requirement: Successful pack operation\n\nThe system SHALL execute a complete pack workflow and report success.\n\n#### Scenario: Complete pack workflow\n- **GIVEN** a valid workspace at `/path/to/agent`\n- **AND** the workspace contains valid Python files\n- **AND** CLI options: `--agent-name my-agent --description \"My agent\"`\n- **WHEN** `pack` command completes successfully\n- **THEN** the CLI SHALL:\n  1. Display a Rich `Progress` spinner during work\n  2. Call `PackRuntime.pack()` with appropriate options\n  3. Validate workspace structure\n  4. Load or create metadata\n  5. Apply CLI overrides\n  6. Validate language compatibility\n  7. Process dependencies\n  8. Generate Dockerfile (if applicable)\n  9. Save updated metadata\n  10. Print success message with:\n      - `agent_name` = `\"my-agent\"`\n      - `workspace_path` = `/path/to/agent`\n      - `metadata_path` = `/path/to/agent/agent_metadata.yaml`\n\n#### Scenario: Pack with verbose output\n- **GIVEN** the user runs `pack --verbose`\n- **WHEN** the command executes\n- **THEN** the system SHALL set logging level to `DEBUG`\n- **AND** print detailed logs including:\n  - Workspace validation steps\n  - Metadata loading/creating steps\n  - Override applications\n  - Dockerfile generation details\n\n---\n\n### Requirement: Pack failure handling\n\nThe system SHALL handle pack errors gracefully with appropriate error messages.\n\n#### Scenario: PackRuntime raises exception\n- **GIVEN** `PackRuntime.pack` raises an exception (e.g., `ValueError(\"Invalid workspace\")`)\n- **AND** verbose is `False`\n- **WHEN** the pack command catches the exception\n- **THEN** `_handle_error` SHALL be called with `(e, \"packing agent\", verbose=False)`\n- **AND** the CLI SHALL print `\"Error packaging agent: Invalid workspace\"` in red\n- **AND** no traceback SHALL be printed\n- **AND** the CLI SHALL exit with code `1`\n\n#### Scenario: PackRuntime raises exception with verbose\n- **GIVEN** `PackRuntime.pack` raises an exception (e.g., `RuntimeError(\"Docker not available\")`)\n- **AND** verbose is `True`\n- **WHEN** the pack command catches the exception\n- **THEN** `_handle_error` SHALL be called with `(e, \"packing agent\", verbose=True)`\n- **AND** the CLI SHALL print `\"Error packaging agent: Docker not available\"` in red\n- **AND** a full traceback SHALL be printed\n- **AND** the CLI SHALL exit with code `1`\n\n---\n\n### Requirement: Integration with PackRuntime\n\nThe system SHALL properly instantiate and call `PackRuntime` from the CLI.\n\n#### Scenario: PackRuntime initialization\n- **GIVEN** the user runs `pack --verbose`\n- **WHEN** the pack command handler executes\n- **THEN** it SHALL instantiate `PackRuntime(verbose=True)`\n\n#### Scenario: PackRuntime method call\n- **GIVEN** CLI options are parsed\n- **WHEN** the pack command handler executes\n- **THEN** it SHALL call `PackRuntime.pack(workspace_path, **options)`\n- **AND** pass all relevant options:\n  - `agent_name`, `language`, `entrypoint`, `port`\n  - `build_mode`, `description`, `output`\n  - `verbose` (from command-local option)\n\n#### Scenario: PackRuntime return value\n- **GIVEN** `PackRuntime.pack` returns `{\"agent_name\": \"my-agent\", \"workspace_path\": \"/path/to/agent\", \"metadata_path\": \"/path/to/agent/agent_metadata.yaml\"}`\n- **WHEN** the pack command handler receives the result\n- **THEN** it SHALL use the returned values for success message formatting\n\n---\n\n## Implementation Notes\n\n### Error Handling Pattern\nAll subcommand errors SHALL be handled via `_handle_error(e, command_name, verbose)`:\n- Print `\"Error {command_name}: {e}\"` in red (Rich markup)\n- If `verbose=True`, print full traceback\n- Raise `typer.Exit(1)`\n\n### Progress Indication\nThe pack command SHOULD use Rich `Progress` or spinner during:\n- Workspace validation\n- Metadata loading/saving\n- Dockerfile generation\n\n### Metadata Precedence\nWhen loading metadata, the precedence SHALL be:\n1. `agent_metadata.yaml` (primary)\n2. `agent.yaml` (fallback)\n3. `metadata.yaml` (fallback)\n4. Create new with defaults (if none exist)\n\n### Language Validation\nThe `AgentMetadata` Pydantic model SHALL validate:\n- `language`: must be `\"python\"` or `\"java\"` (case-insensitive, normalized to lowercase)\n- `build_mode`: must be `\"local\"` or `\"cloud\"` (case-insensitive, normalized to lowercase)\n- `port`: must be between 1 and 65535\n\n---\n\n## File Index\n\n| Path | Purpose |\n|------|---------|\n| `agentcube/cli/main.py` | Typer app with pack command definition |\n| `agentcube/runtime/pack_runtime.py` | `PackRuntime` class implementation |\n| `agentcube/services/metadata_service.py` | `AgentMetadata` Pydantic model |\n| `agentcube/models/pack_models.py` | `MetadataOptions` dataclass |\n\n---\n\n## Dependencies\n\n| Dependency | Purpose |\n|------------|---------|\n| `typer` | CLI framework |\n| `pydantic` | Data validation for AgentMetadata |\n| `pyyaml` | YAML parsing and generation |\n| `rich` | Progress indicators and formatted output |\n\n---\n\n## Related Specifications\n\n- `cli-toolkit/design.md` — CLI package layout and class definitions\n- `cli-toolkit/spec.md` — Full CLI specification with all commands\n"},"output":"Wrote file successfully.","metadata":{"diagnostics":{"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-kimi-k2.5_20260410T163138Z/changes/AR-020/spec.yaml":[]},"filepath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-kimi-k2.5_20260410T163138Z/changes/AR-020/delta-spec.md","exists":false,"truncated":false},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-kimi-k2.5_20260410T163138Z/changes/AR-020/delta-spec.md","time":{"start":1775884892959,"end":1775884892969}}}}
